abstract_summ: Following the emergence of a novel coronavirus1 (SARS-CoV-2) and its spread outside of China, Europe has experienced large epidemics . In response, many European countries have implemented unprecedented non-pharmaceutical interventions such as closure of schools and national lockdowns . We study the impact of major interventions across 11 European countries for the period from the start of COVID-19 until the 4th of May 2020 .
